HEADWORD: Spoondrift
<hw>Spoon"drift</hw> <pr>(-dr⟦icr⟧ft)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spoom</ets> + <ets>drift</ets>.]</ety> <def>Spray blown from
the tops of waves during a gale at sea; also, snow driven in the wind at
sea; -- <altsp>written also <asp>spindrift</asp></altsp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

